balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

baseURI().details: Returns the base URI for metadata.

burnLeaf(address,uint48).details: Burns a leaf from a user's tree and mints ERC20 tokens for the user.

params.treeID: ID of the tree. Emits {TransferSingle}, {BurnLeaf}, {TreeOutworn} events.

leafBalance(address,uint48).details: Returns the number of leaves remaining in a user's specific tree.

mintTree(address,bytes).details: Mints a default tree with 50 leaves and a price of 1 token per leaf.

mintTree(address,uint48,uint256,bytes).details: Mints a new tree for user `to` with a specified `leafAmount` number of leaves and `leafPrice` price per leaf.

params.leafAmount: Number of leaves in the tree.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setBaseURI(string).details: Sets the base URI for metadata.

setTokenURI(uint256,string).details: Sets a specific URI for a given token ID.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

treeIDs(address).details: Returns the list of tree IDs owned by a user sorted by ascending.

uri(uint256).details: Returns the URI for a given token ID.

mintTree(address,bytes).notice: Tree is represented as a leaf collection where each leaf has its tree ID as first 128 bits, and its ID in the tree as second 128 bit half. Emits {MintTree} event.

mintTree(address,uint48,uint256,bytes).notice: Tree is represented as a leaf collection where each leaf has its tree ID as first 128 bits, and its ID in the tree as second 128 bit half. Emits {MintTree} event.
